    {
      "id": "4",
      "source_id": "47",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "What causes a port to be placed in the err-disabled state?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "latency",
        "B": "nothing plugged into the port",
        "C": "shutdown command issued on the port (administratively down)",
        "D": "port security violation"
      },
      "answer": [
        "D"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "When a port security is violated, that port can be put into errdisable state.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Điều gì khiến một port bị đặt vào trạng thái err-disabled?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Độ trễ (latency)",
        "B": "Không có gì được cắm vào port",
        "C": "Lệnh shutdown được thực thi trên port (administratively down)",
        "D": "Vi phạm port security"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "5",
      "source_id": "36",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "What is the default port-security behavior on a trunk link?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "It causes a network loop when a violation occurs.",
        "B": "It disables the native VLAN configuration as soon as port security is enabled.",
        "C": "It places the port in the err-disabled state if it learns more than one MAC address.",
        "D": "It places the port in the err-disabled state after 10 MAC addresses are statically configured."
      },
      "answer": [
        "C"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "We tested it with IOS v15.2 and this is the result:\nWe can see the “Maximum MAC Addresses” is 1 so this port will be put in the err-disabled state if\nit learns more than one MAC address.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Hành vi mặc định của port-security trên một trunk link là gì?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Nó gây ra vòng lặp mạng (network loop) khi xảy ra vi phạm.",
        "B": "Nó vô hiệu hóa cấu hình native VLAN ngay khi port security được bật.",
        "C": "Nó đặt port vào trạng thái err-disabled nếu học được nhiều hơn một MAC address.",
        "D": "Nó đặt port vào trạng thái err-disabled sau khi 10 MAC address được cấu hình tĩnh."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "6",
      "source_id": "42",
      "type": "multi",
      "question": "Refer to the exhibit.\nA network engineer started to configure port security on a new switch. These requirements must\nbe met:\n– MAC addresses must be learned dynamically.\n– Log messages must be generated without disabling the interface when unwanted traffic is seen.\nWhich two commands must be configured to complete this task? (Choose two)",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security mac-address 0010.7B84.45E6",
        "B": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security maximum 2",
        "C": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security mac-address sticky",
        "D": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security violation shutdown",
        "E": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security violation restrict"
      },
      "answer": [
        "B",
        "E"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "The requirement said MAC addresses must be learned dynamically so we cannot assign a specific\nMAC address or use the “sticky” keyword -> Answer A and answer C are not correct. Also the\nrequirement said “MAC addresses” in plural so we set the maximum to 2 -> Answer B is correct.\n“Log messages must be generated without disabling the interface” -> use “restrict” keyword for\nviolation, not “shutdown” keyword -> Answer E is correct.\nNote:\nYou can configure the interface for one of these violation modes, based on the action to be taken if\na violation occurs:\n+ Restrict – A port security violation restricts data, causes the SecurityViolation counter to\nincrement, and causes an SNMP Notification to be generated.\n+ Shutdown – A port security violation causes the interface to shut down immediately. When a\nsecure port is in the error-disabled state, you can bring it out of this state by entering the\nerrdisable recovery cause psecure_violation global configuration command or you can manually\nreenable it by entering the shutdown and no shut down interface configuration commands. This is\nthe default mode.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Tham khảo hình minh họa.\nMột kỹ sư mạng bắt đầu cấu hình port security trên một switch mới. Các yêu cầu sau phải được đáp ứng:\n– MAC address phải được học động.\n– Phải tạo log message mà không tắt interface khi phát hiện traffic không mong muốn.\nHai lệnh nào phải được cấu hình để hoàn thành nhiệm vụ này? (Chọn hai)",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security mac-address 0010.7B84.45E6",
        "B": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security maximum 2",
        "C": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security mac-address sticky",
        "D": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security violation shutdown",
        "E": "SW(config-if)#switchport port-security violation restrict"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "7",
