      "id": "17",
      "source_id": "28",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Refer to the exhibit.\nOption A Option B\nip access-list standard 99 ip access-list standard 99\npermit 10.100.100.0 permit 10.100.100.0\n0.0.0.255 0.0.0.255\ndeny 192.168.0.0 deny 192.168.0.0\n0.0.255.255 0.255.255.255\nOption C Option D\nip access-list standard 100 ip access-list standard 199\npermit 10.100.100.0 permit 10.100.100.0\n0.0.0.255 0.0.0.255\ndeny 192.168.0.0 deny 192.168.0.0\n0.255.255.255 0.0.255.255\nAn access list is required to permit traffic from any host on interface G0/0 and deny traffic from\ninterface Gi0/1. Which access list must be applied?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "Option A",
        "B": "Option B",
        "C": "Option C",
        "D": "Option D"
      },
      "answer": [
        "A"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "The standard access lists are ranged from 1 to 99 and from 1300 to 1999 so only Option A & B are\ncorrect. The subnet on interface Gi0/1 is 192.168.0.0/16 so we have to use the ACL statement\n“deny 192.168.0.0 0.0.255.255“",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Tham khảo hình minh họa.\nOption A Option B\nip access-list standard 99 ip access-list standard 99\npermit 10.100.100.0 permit 10.100.100.0\n0.0.0.255 0.0.0.255\ndeny 192.168.0.0 deny 192.168.0.0\n0.0.255.255 0.255.255.255\nOption C Option D\nip access-list standard 100 ip access-list standard 199\npermit 10.100.100.0 permit 10.100.100.0\n0.0.0.255 0.0.0.255\ndeny 192.168.0.0 deny 192.168.0.0\n0.255.255.255 0.0.255.255\nMột access list được yêu cầu để cho phép traffic từ bất kỳ host nào trên interface G0/0 và từ chối traffic từ interface Gi0/1. Access list nào phải được áp dụng?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Option A",
        "B": "Option B",
        "C": "Option C",
        "D": "Option D"
      }
    },
