      "question": "After installing a new Cisco ISE server, which task must the engineer perform on the Cisco WLC to\nconnect wireless clients on a specific VLAN based on their credentials?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "Enable the Authorized MIC APs against auth-list or AAA.",
        "B": "Enable the allow AAA Override",
        "C": "Disable the LAG Mode or Next Reboot.",
        "D": "Enable the Event Driven RRM."
      },
      "answer": [
        "B"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "Dynamic VLAN assignment is one such feature that places a wireless user into a specific VLAN\nbased on the credentials supplied by the user. This task of assigning users to a specific VLAN is\nhandled by a RADIUS authentication server, such as Cisco ISE. This can be used, for example, to\nallow the wireless host to remain on the same VLAN as it moves within a campus network.\n…\nIn order to accomplish dynamic VLAN assignment with WLCs based on ISE to AD group mapping,\nthese steps must be performed:\n+ ISE to AD integration and configuration of authentication and authorization policies for users on\nISE\n+ WLC configuration to support dot1x authentication and AAA override for SSID ‘office_hq’\n+ End client supplicant configuration\nReference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/wireless/4400-series-wireless-lan-\ncontrollers/99121-vlan-acs-ad-config.html",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Sau khi cài đặt Cisco ISE server mới, kỹ sư phải thực hiện tác vụ nào trên Cisco WLC để kết nối các wireless client vào một VLAN cụ thể dựa trên thông tin đăng nhập của họ?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Bật Authorized MIC APs against auth-list hoặc AAA.",
        "B": "Bật allow AAA Override",
        "C": "Tắt LAG Mode hoặc Next Reboot.",
        "D": "Bật Event Driven RRM."
      }
    },
