    {
      "id": "37",
      "source_id": "24",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "How are VLAN hopping attacks mitigated?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "manually implement trunk ports and disable DTP",
        "B": "configure extended VLANs",
        "C": "activate all ports and place in the default VLAN",
        "D": "enable dynamic ARP inspection"
      },
      "answer": [
        "A"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "VLAN Hopping: By altering the VLAN ID on packets encapsulated for trunking, an attacking\ndevice can send or receive packets on various VLANs, bypassing Layer 3 security measures. VLAN\nhopping can be accomplished by switch spoofing or double tagging.\na. Switch spoofing:\nThe attacker can connect an unauthorized Cisco switch to a Company switch port. The\nunauthorized switch can send DTP frames and form a trunk with the Company Switch. If the\nattacker can establish a trunk link to the Company switch, it receives traffic to all VLANs through\nthe trunk because all VLANs are allowed on a trunk by default.\n(Instead of using a Cisco Switch, the attacker can use a software to create and send DTP frames).\nTo mitigate this type of attack, we can disable DTP.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Các cuộc tấn công VLAN hopping được giảm thiểu như thế nào?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Cấu hình thủ công các trunk port và tắt DTP",
        "B": "Cấu hình extended VLAN",
        "C": "Kích hoạt tất cả các port và đặt vào default VLAN",
        "D": "Bật dynamic ARP inspection"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "38",
      "source_id": "11",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Which device tracks the state of active connections in order to make a decision to forward a packet\nthrough?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "firewall",
        "B": "wireless access point",
        "C": "router",
        "D": "wireless LAN controller"
      },
      "answer": [
        "A"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "Stateful inspection firewalls keep track of connection status. Ports can be dynamically opened and\nclosed if necessary for completing a transaction. For example, when you make a connection to a\nserver using HTTP, the server will initiate a new connection back to your system on a random port.\nA stateful inspection firewall will automatically open a port for this return connection.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Thiết bị nào theo dõi trạng thái của các kết nối đang hoạt động để đưa ra quyết định chuyển tiếp packet?",
