      "id": "63",
      "source_id": "77",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "A Cisco engineer is configuring a factory-default router with these three passwords:\n* The user EXEC password for console access is p4ssw0rd1.\n* The user EXEC password for Telnet access is s3cr3t2.\n* The password for privileged EXEC mode is priv4t3p4ss.\nWhich command sequence must the engineer configure?\nOption A Option B\nenable secret priv4t3p4ss enable secret privilege 15\n! priv4t3p4ss\nline con 0 !\npassword p4ssw0rd1 line con 0\nlogin password p4ssw0rdi\n! login\nline vty 0 15 !\npassword s3cr3t2 line vty 0 15\nlogin password s3cr3t2\nlogin\nOption C Option D\nenable secret priv413p4ss enable secret priv4t3p4ss\n! !\nline con 0 line con 0\npassword login p4ssw0rd1 password p4ssw0rd1\n! !\nline vty 0 15 line vty 0 15\npassword login s3cr3t2 password s3cr3t2\nlogin",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "Option A",
        "B": "Option B",
        "C": "Option C",
        "D": "Option D"
      },
      "answer": [
        "A"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "There is no “enable secret privilege 15 …” command.\nIf we enter the “enable secret privilege 15 priv4t3p4ss” command then the text “privilege 15\npriv4t3p4ss” will be used as password. In both console and vty line we should use the “login”\ncommand to enable password checking.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Một kỹ sư Cisco đang cấu hình một router mặc định nhà máy với ba mật khẩu sau:\n* Mật khẩu user EXEC cho truy cập console là p4ssw0rd1.\n* Mật khẩu user EXEC cho truy cập Telnet là s3cr3t2.\n* Mật khẩu cho privileged EXEC mode là priv4t3p4ss.\nChuỗi lệnh nào kỹ sư phải cấu hình?\nOption A Option B\nenable secret priv4t3p4ss enable secret privilege 15\n! priv4t3p4ss\nline con 0 !\npassword p4ssw0rd1 line con 0\nlogin password p4ssw0rdi\n! login\nline vty 0 15 !\npassword s3cr3t2 line vty 0 15\nlogin password s3cr3t2\nlogin\nOption C Option D\nenable secret priv413p4ss enable secret priv4t3p4ss\n! !\nline con 0 line con 0\npassword login p4ssw0rd1 password p4ssw0rd1\n! !\nline vty 0 15 line vty 0 15\npassword login s3cr3t2 password s3cr3t2\nlogin",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Option A",
        "B": "Option B",
        "C": "Option C",
        "D": "Option D"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "64",
      "source_id": "85",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Which field within the access-request packet is encrypted by RADIUS?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "authorized services",
        "B": "authenticator",
        "C": "username",
        "D": "password"
      },
      "answer": [
        "D"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "RADIUS encrypts only the password in the access-request packet, from the client to the server.\nThe remainder of the packet is unencrypted. Other information, such as username, authorized\nservices, and accounting, can be captured by a third party.\nReference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/security-vpn/remote-authentication-dial-\nuser-service-radius/13838-10.html",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Trường nào trong gói access-request được RADIUS mã hóa?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Dịch vụ được ủy quyền (authorized services)",
        "B": "Authenticator",
        "C": "Username",
        "D": "Mật khẩu (password)"
      }
    },
