    {
      "id": "90",
      "source_id": "5",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Refer to the exhibit. If the network environment is operating normally, which type of device must\nbe connected to interface FastEthernet 0/1?\nip arp inspection vlan 2-10\ninterface fastethernet 0/1\nip arp inspection trust",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "DHCP client",
        "B": "access point",
        "C": "router",
        "D": "PC"
      },
      "answer": [
        "C"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "To configure DHCP snooping feature, at least three steps must be done:\nSequence and Description Command\n1. Configure global DHCP snooping Switch(config)# ip dhcp snooping\n2. Configure trusted ports (as least on Switch(config-if)# ip dhcp snooping trust\n1 port).\nBy default, all ports are untrusted\n3. Configure DHCP snooping for the Switch(config)# ip dhcp snooping vlan {VLAN-\nselected VLANs ID | VLAN range}\nNote: To configure DHCP snooping with Dynamic ARP Inspection we need to add the command “ip\narp inspection vlan vlan-id” in global configuration mode and “ip arp inspection trust” in interface\nmode.\nIn a normal network environment, we should trust interfaces that are connected to routers, not\nend points.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Tham khảo hình minh họa. Nếu môi trường mạng đang hoạt động bình thường, loại thiết bị nào phải được kết nối với interface FastEthernet 0/1?\nip arp inspection vlan 2-10\ninterface fastethernet 0/1\nip arp inspection trust",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "DHCP client",
        "B": "Access point",
        "C": "Router",
        "D": "PC"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "91",
      "source_id": "1",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Refer to the exhibit. What is the effect of this configuration?\nip arp inspection vlan 2\ninterface fastethernet 0/1\nswitchport mode access\nswitchport access vlan 2",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "All ARP packets are dropped by the switch",
        "B": "Egress traffic is passed only if the destination is a DHCP server.",
        "C": "All ingress and egress traffic is dropped because the interface is untrusted",
        "D": "The switch discard all ingress ARP traffic with invalid MAC-to-IP address bindings"
      },
      "answer": [
        "D"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "Dynamic ARP inspection is an ingress security feature; it does not perform any egress checking.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Tham khảo hình minh họa. Tác dụng của cấu hình này là gì?\nip arp inspection vlan 2\ninterface fastethernet 0/1\nswitchport mode access\nswitchport access vlan 2",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Tất cả ARP packet bị switch loại bỏ",
        "B": "Traffic egress chỉ được cho qua nếu đích là DHCP server.",
        "C": "Tất cả traffic ingress và egress bị loại bỏ vì interface không được tin cậy",
        "D": "Switch loại bỏ tất cả ARP traffic ingress có liên kết MAC-to-IP không hợp lệ"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "92",
      "source_id": "2",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Refer to the exhibit. What is the effect of this configuration?\nip arp inspection vlan 2\ninterface fastethernet 0/1\nswitchport mode access\nswitchport access vlan 2",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "The switch port interface trust state becomes untrusted",
        "B": "The switch port remains administratively down until the interface is connected to another switch",
        "C": "Dynamic ARP inspection is disabled because the ARP ACL is missing",
        "D": "The switch port remains down until it is configured to trust or untrust incoming packets"
      },
      "answer": [
        "A"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "Dynamic ARP inspection (DAI) is a security feature that validates ARP packets in a network. It\nintercepts, logs, and discards ARP packets with invalid IP-to-MAC address bindings. This capability\nprotects the network from certain man-in-the-middle attacks. After enabling DAI, all ports become\nuntrusted ports.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Tham khảo hình minh họa. Tác dụng của cấu hình này là gì?\nip arp inspection vlan 2\ninterface fastethernet 0/1\nswitchport mode access\nswitchport access vlan 2",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Trạng thái tin cậy của switch port interface trở thành untrusted",
        "B": "Switch port vẫn ở trạng thái administratively down cho đến khi interface được kết nối với switch khác",
        "C": "Dynamic ARP inspection bị tắt vì thiếu ARP ACL",
        "D": "Switch port vẫn down cho đến khi được cấu hình để tin cậy hoặc không tin cậy các packet đến"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "93",
      "source_id": "36",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Refer to the exhibit.\nThe DHCP server and clients are connected to the same switch. What is the next step to complete\nthe DHCP configuration to allow clients on VLAN 1 to receive addresses from the DHCP server?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "Configure the ip dhcp snooping trust command on the interface that is connected to the\nDHCP server",
        "B": "Configure the ip dhcp relay information option command on the interface that is connected\nto the DHCP server",
        "C": "Configure the ip dhcp relay information option command on the interface that is connected\nto the DHCP client",
        "D": "Configure the ip dhcp snooping trust command on the interface that is connected to the\nDHCP client"
      },
      "answer": [
        "A"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "We see from the output of the “show ip dhcp snooping statistics detail” command the packets\n“received on untrusted ports = 32” so maybe the interface connected to DHCP Server is configured\nuntrusted port. Therefore we have to configure the “ip dhcp snooping trust” command on this\ninterface.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Tham khảo hình minh họa.\nDHCP server và các client được kết nối với cùng một switch. Bước tiếp theo để hoàn thành cấu hình DHCP cho phép các client trên VLAN 1 nhận địa chỉ từ DHCP server là gì?",
      "options_vi": {
