      "explanation": "Whenever you want to control which devices can talk to the main CPU, a CPU ACL is used.\nNote: CPU ACLs only filter traffic towards the CPU, and not any traffic exiting or generated by the\nCPU.\nReference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/wireless/4400-series-wireless-lan-\ncontrollers/109669-secure-wlc.html",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Tính năng nào trên Cisco Wireless LAN Controller khi được bật sẽ hạn chế quyền truy cập quản lý từ các mạng cụ thể?",
