    {
      "id": "122",
      "source_id": "8",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "An administrator must secure the WLC from receiving spoofed association requests. Which steps\nmust be taken to configure the WLC to restrict the requests and force the user to wait 10 ms to\nretry an association request?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "Enable Security Association Teardown Protection and set the SA Query timeout to 10",
        "B": "Enable the Protected Management Frame service and set the Comeback timer to 10",
        "C": "Enable 802.1x Layer 2 security and set the Comeback timer to 10",
        "D": "Enable MAC filtering and set the SA Query timeout to 10"
      },
      "answer": [
        "B"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "Comeback timer specifies the time which an associated client must wait before the association can\nbe tried again when first denied with a status code 30.\nSA query timeout specifies the amount of time the WLC waits for a response from the client for the\nquery process.\nReference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/wireless-mobility/wireless-lan-\nwlan/212576-configure-802-11w-management-frame-prote.html\nNote: We can use either 802.1x or PSK as the authentication key management method so answer\nC is not correct.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Quản trị viên phải bảo mật WLC khỏi nhận các yêu cầu association giả mạo. Các bước nào phải thực hiện để cấu hình WLC hạn chế các yêu cầu và buộc người dùng chờ 10 ms trước khi thử lại yêu cầu association?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Bật Security Association Teardown Protection và đặt SA Query timeout thành 10",
        "B": "Bật dịch vụ Protected Management Frame và đặt Comeback timer thành 10",
        "C": "Bật bảo mật Layer 2 802.1x và đặt Comeback timer thành 10",
        "D": "Bật MAC filtering và đặt SA Query timeout thành 10"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "123",
      "source_id": "10",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Which 802.11 management frame type is sent when a client roams between access points on the\nsame SSID?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "Authentication Request",
        "B": "Probe Request",
        "C": "Reassociation Request",
        "D": "Association Request"
      },
      "answer": [
        "C"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "Association request frame – (0x00) Sent from a wireless client, it enables the AP to allocate\nresources and synchronize. The frame carries information about the wireless connection including\nsupported data rates and SSID of the network to the wireless client that wants to associate. If the\nrequest is accepted, the AP reserves memory and establishes an association ID for the device.\nAssociation response frame – (0x01) Sent from an AP to a wireless client containing the\nacceptance or rejection to an association request. If it is an acceptance, the frame contains\ninformation, such as an association ID and supported data rates.\nReassociation request frame – (0x02) A device sends a reassociation request when it drops\nfrom range of the currently associated AP and finds another AP with a stronger signal. The new AP\ncoordinates the forwarding of any information that may still be contained in the buffer of the\nprevious AP.\nReassociation response frame – (0x03) Sent from an AP containing the acceptance or rejection\nto a device reassociation request frame. The frame includes information required for association,\nsuch as the association ID and supported data rates.\nProbe request frame – (0x04) Sent from a wireless client when it requires information from\nanother wireless client.\nAuthentication frame – (0x0B) The sending device sends an authentication frame to the AP\ncontaining its identity.\nReference: https://www.ii.pwr.edu.pl/~kano/course/module8/8.2.1.4/8.2.1.4.html",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Loại management frame 802.11 nào được gửi khi client chuyển vùng (roam) giữa các access point trên cùng SSID?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Authentication Request",
        "B": "Probe Request",
        "C": "Reassociation Request",
        "D": "Association Request"
      }
    },
