      "id": "126",
      "source_id": "30",
      "type": "multi",
      "question": "Which two protocols are supported on service-port interfaces? (Choose two)",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "RADIUS",
        "B": "TACACS+",
        "C": "Telnet",
        "D": "SCP",
        "E": "SSH"
      },
      "answer": [
        "C",
        "E"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "The service-port interface controls communications through and is statically mapped by the\nsystem to the service port. The service port can be used for out-of-band management.\nThe service port can obtain an IPv4 address using DHCP, or it can be assigned a static IPv4\naddress, but a default gateway cannot be assigned to the service-port interface. Static IPv4 routes\ncan be defined through the controller for remote network access to the service port.\nIf the service port is in use, the management interface must be on a different supernet from the\nservice-port interface.\nThe service-port interface supports the following protocols:\n+ SSH and Telnet\n+ HTTP and HTTPS\n+ SNMP\n+ FTP, TFTP, and SFTP\n+ Syslog\n+ ICMP (ping)\n+ NTP\nNote: TACACS+ and RADIUS are not supported through the service port.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Hai giao thức nào được hỗ trợ trên service-port interface? (Chọn hai)",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "RADIUS",
        "B": "TACACS+",
        "C": "Telnet",
        "D": "SCP",
        "E": "SSH"
      }
    },
    {
