      "type": "single",
      "question": "Which mode must be set for APs to communicate to a Wireless LAN Controller using the Control\nand Provisioning of Wireless Access Points (CAPWAP) protocol?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "bridge",
        "B": "route",
        "C": "autonomous",
        "D": "lightweight"
      },
      "answer": [
        "D"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "Cisco Access Points (APs) can operate in one of two modes: autonomous or lightweight\n+ Autonomous: self-sufficient and standalone. Used for small wireless networks.\n+ Lightweight: A Cisco lightweight AP (LAP) has to join a Wireless LAN Controller (WLC) to\nfunction. LAP and WLC communicate with each other via a logical pair of CAPWAP tunnels.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Chế độ nào phải được đặt cho AP để giao tiếp với Wireless LAN Controller sử dụng giao thức Control and Provisioning of Wireless Access Points (CAPWAP)?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Bridge",
        "B": "Route",
        "C": "Autonomous",
        "D": "Lightweight"
      }
    },
