    {
      "id": "158",
      "source_id": "34",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Refer to the exhibit.\nClients on the WLAN are required to use 802.11r. What action must be taken to meet the\nrequirement?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "Enable CCKM under Authentication Key Management",
        "B": "Under Protected Management Frames, set the PMF option to Required",
        "C": "Set the Fast Transition option to Enable and enable FT 802.1X under Authentication Key\nManagement",
        "D": "Set the Fast Transition option and the WPA gtk-randomize State to disable"
      },
      "answer": [
        "C"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "Configuring 802.11r Fast Transition (GUI)\nProcedure\nStep 1 Choose WLANs to open the WLANs window.\nStep 2 Click a WLAN ID to open the WLANs > Edit window.\nStep 3 Choose Security > Layer 2 tab.\nStep 4 From the Layer 2 Security drop-down list, choose WPA+WPA2.\nThe Authentication Key Management parameters for Fast Transition are displayed.\nStep 5 From the Fast Transition drop-down list, choose Fast Transition on the WLAN.\nStep 6 Check or uncheck the Over the DS check box to enable or disable Fast Transition over a\ndistributed system.\nThis option is available only if you enable Fast Transition or if Fast Transition is adaptive.\nTo use 802.11r Fast Transition over-the-air and over-the-ds must be disabled.\nStep 7 In the Reassociation Timeout field, enter the number of seconds after which the\nreassociation attempt of a client to an AP should time out. The valid range is 1 to 100 seconds.\nNote: This option is available only if you enable Fast Transition.\nStep 8 Under Authentication Key Management, choose FT 802.1X or FT PSK.\nReference: https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/technotes/80211r-\nft/b-80211r-dg.html\nFast BSS Transition (802.11r, often abbreviated to Fast Transition or FT) describes mechanisms by\nwhich a mobile device can reestablish existing security and/or QoS parameters prior to\nreassociating to a new AP. These mechanisms are referred to as “fast” because they seek to\nsignificantly reduce the length of time that connectivity is interrupted between a mobile device and\nWi-Fi infrastructure when that mobile device is connecting to a new AP. Please note that the\nprocess of disconnecting from one AP and connecting to another AP is formally designated as a\n“BSS transition”. Therefore, the protocols established by FT apply to mobile device transitions\nbetween APs only within the same mobility domain and within the same ESS (ESS transition is out\nof scope for FT)\nReference: https://blogs.cisco.com/networking/what-is-802-11r-why-is-this-important",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Tham khảo hình minh họa.\nCác client trên WLAN được yêu cầu sử dụng 802.11r. Hành động nào phải thực hiện để đáp ứng yêu cầu?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Bật CCKM trong Authentication Key Management",
        "B": "Trong Protected Management Frames, đặt tùy chọn PMF thành Required",
        "C": "Đặt tùy chọn Fast Transition thành Enable và bật FT 802.1X trong Authentication Key Management",
        "D": "Đặt tùy chọn Fast Transition và WPA gtk-randomize State thành disable"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "159",
      "source_id": "47",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "What must be considered for a locally switched FlexConnect AP if the VLANs that are used by the\nAP and client access are different?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "The APs must be connected to the switch with multiple links in LAG mode.",
        "B": "The native VLAN must match the management VLAN of the AP.",
        "C": "The switch port mode must be set to trunk.",
        "D": "IEEE 802.1Q trunking must be disabled on the switch port."
      },
      "answer": [
        "C"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "FlexConnect VLANs and ACLs\nYou can configure the LAN uplink interface of a FlexConnect AP as either an access port or as a\ntrunk. If you configure the interface as an access port, then the AP’s management traffic and all\nclient traffic, whether centrally or locally switched, will be in the same VLAN. For security and\nreliability reasons, we recommend that you segregate the client traffic from the management\nVLAN, and so to configure the AP’s switchport as a trunk, with separately tagged VLANs for locally\nswitched client traffic.\nReference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/8-5/config-\nguide/b_cg85/flexconnect.html\nAnswer B is not correct as it should be “The native VLAN must match the native VLAN of the AP”\n(not the management VLAN).",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Điều gì phải được xem xét cho một FlexConnect AP chuyển mạch cục bộ nếu các VLAN được sử dụng bởi AP và client access khác nhau?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Các AP phải được kết nối với switch bằng nhiều liên kết ở chế độ LAG.",
        "B": "Native VLAN phải khớp với management VLAN của AP.",
        "C": "Chế độ switch port phải được đặt thành trunk.",
        "D": "IEEE 802.1Q trunking phải bị tắt trên switch port."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "160",
      "source_id": "48",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Which command configures the Cisco WLC to prevent a serial session with the WLC CLI from being\nautomatically logged out?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "config sessions maxsessions 0",
        "B": "config serial timeout 9600",
        "C": "config serial timeout 0",
        "D": "config sessions timeout 0"
      },
      "answer": [
        "C"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "The CLI automatically logs you out without saving any changes after 5 minutes of inactivity. You\ncan set the automatic logout from 0 (never log out) to 160 minutes using the config serial\ntimeout command.\nTo prevent SSH or Telnet sessions from timing out, run the config sessions timeout\n0 command.\nReference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/8-0/configuration-\nguide/b_cg80/b_cg80_chapter_011.html\nThis question asks about the serial session so the first command is the correct answer.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Lệnh nào cấu hình Cisco WLC để ngăn phiên serial với WLC CLI bị tự động đăng xuất?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "config sessions maxsessions 0",
        "B": "config serial timeout 9600",
        "C": "config serial timeout 0",
        "D": "config sessions timeout 0"
      }
    },
