      "id": "164",
      "source_id": "57",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Refer to the exhibit.\nWireless LAN access must be set up to force all clients from the NA WLAN to authenticate against\nthe local database. The WLAN is configured for local EAP authentication. The time that users\naccess the network must not be limited. Which action completes this configuration?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "Check the Guest User Role check box",
        "B": "Clear the Lifetime (seconds) value",
        "C": "Set the Lifetime (seconds) value to 0",
        "D": "Uncheck the Guest User check box"
      },
      "answer": [
        "D"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "The users created in the “Local Net Users” are stored in the local database. With the “Guest User”\ncheck box enabled, we have to set the time for that user. The “Lifetime” is the amount of time that\nthe guest user account is to remain active. The valid range is 60 to 2,592,000 seconds (30 days)\ninclusive, and the default setting is 86,400 seconds.\nIf we don’t want to limit the time for that user, uncheck the “Guest User” check box.\n===============================",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Tham khảo hình minh họa.\nQuyền truy cập WLAN phải được thiết lập để buộc tất cả client từ NA WLAN xác thực với local database. WLAN được cấu hình cho xác thực EAP cục bộ. Thời gian người dùng truy cập mạng không được giới hạn. Hành động nào hoàn thành cấu hình này?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Chọn hộp kiểm Guest User Role",
        "B": "Xóa giá trị Lifetime (seconds)",
        "C": "Đặt giá trị Lifetime (seconds) thành 0",
        "D": "Bỏ chọn hộp kiểm Guest User"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "165",
      "source_id": "62",
      "type": "multi",
      "question": "Which two functions does a WLC perform in the lightweight access-point architecture that an AP\nperforms independently in an autonomous architecture? (Choose two)",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "handling the association, authentication, and roaming of wireless clients",
        "B": "encrypting and decrypting traffic that uses the WAP protocol family",
        "C": "preventing collisions between wireless clients on the same RF channel",
        "D": "managing RF channels, including transmission power",
        "E": "sending and processing beacon frames"
      },
      "answer": [
        "A",
        "D"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "This question asks what the WLC can do for the AP or which functions are moved from AP to WLC\nin lightweight access-point architecture.\nThe wireless clients encrypt and decrypt the traffic, not the AP -> Answer B is not correct.\nThe wireless clients also run CSMA/CA to prevent collisions between them, not the AP -> Answer C\nis not correct.\nWith wireless networking, we have real-time and management functions. The AP should handle\nreal-time functions, but everything that is not delay-sensitive can do from a central location. We\nseparate the following management and real-time functions of the AP:\n+ Management functions:\n++ Client authentication (-> Answer A is correct)\n++ Security management\n++ Association and reassociation (roaming)\n++ Quality of Service (QoS)\n+ Real-time functions:\n++ Transmission of 802.11 frames\n++ MAC management\n++ Encryption\nSince these functions are not real-time, we can move them to a central point, the WLC. We take\naway some of the intelligence of the AP, which is why we call them lightweight APs (LAP). We\nmove this intelligence to the WLC.\nReference: https://networklessons.com/cisco/ccna-200-301/cisco-wireless-network-architectures\nRadio Resource Management (RRM) allows the controller to dynamically control power and channel\nassignment of APs -> Answer D is correct.\nReference: https://what-when-how.com/deploying-and-troubleshooting-cisco-wireless-lan-\ncontrollers/lightweight-compared-to-traditional-autonomous-aps-cisco-wireless-lan-controllers/",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Hai chức năng nào mà WLC thực hiện trong kiến trúc lightweight access-point mà AP thực hiện độc lập trong kiến trúc autonomous? (Chọn hai)",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Xử lý association, xác thực và roaming của các wireless client",
        "B": "Mã hóa và giải mã traffic sử dụng họ giao thức WAP",
        "C": "Ngăn chặn xung đột giữa các wireless client trên cùng kênh RF",
        "D": "Quản lý các kênh RF, bao gồm công suất phát",
        "E": "Gửi và xử lý beacon frame"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "166",
      "source_id": "77",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "A network administrator plans an update to the Wi-Fi networks in multiple branch offices. Each\nlocation is configured with an SSID called “Office”. The administrator wants every user who\nconnects to the SSID at any location to have the same access level. What must be set the same\non each network to meet the requirement?",
      "question_images": [],
