      "id": "177",
      "source_id": "54",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "Refer to the exhibit.\nA network engineer is configuring a WLAN to connect with the 172.16.10.0/24 network on VLAN\n20. The engineer wants to limit the number of devices that connect to the WLAN on the USERWL\nSSID to 125. Which configuration must the engineer perform on the WLC?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "In the WLAN configuration, set the Maximum Allowed Clients value to 125.",
        "B": "In the Advanced configuration, set the DTIM value to 125.",
