      "type": "single",
      "question": "Which interface or port on the WLC is the default for in-band device administration and\ncommunications between the controller and access points?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "virtual interface",
        "B": "management interface",
        "C": "console port",
        "D": "service port"
      },
      "answer": [
        "B"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "The management interface is the default interface for in-band management of the controller and\nconnectivity to enterprise services such as AAA servers. It is also used for communications\nbetween the controller and access points, for all CAPWAP or intercontroller mobility messaging and\ntunneling traffic.\nReference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/wireless/controller/7-\n4/configuration/guides/consolidated/b_cg74_CONSOLIDATED/b_cg74_CONSOLIDATED_chapter_0\n10011011.html",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Interface hoặc port nào trên WLC là mặc định cho quản trị thiết bị in-band và giao tiếp giữa controller và các access point?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Virtual interface",
        "B": "Management interface",
        "C": "Console port",
        "D": "Service port"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "179",
      "source_id": "63",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "A company has each office using wireless access with multiple SSIDs while limiting roaming\ncapabilities, covering different locations on the internal office LAN, guest networks, and BYOD\naccess for employees. Which change must be enabled to improve the customer experience during\nSSID changes?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "Assisted Roaming Prediction Optimization",
        "B": "Fast Transition",
        "C": "Neighbor List Dual Band",
        "D": "Fast SSID Change"
      },
      "answer": [
        "D"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "“When you enable Fast SSID Change, the controller allows clients to move between SSIDs. When\nthe client sends a new association request for a different SSID, the client entry in the controller\nconnection table is cleared before the client is added to the new SSID.",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Một công ty có mỗi văn phòng sử dụng wireless access với nhiều SSID trong khi giới hạn khả năng roaming, bao gồm các vị trí khác nhau trên LAN văn phòng nội bộ, mạng khách và truy cập BYOD cho nhân viên. Thay đổi nào phải được bật để cải thiện trải nghiệm khách hàng khi thay đổi SSID?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "Assisted Roaming Prediction Optimization",
        "B": "Fast Transition",
        "C": "Neighbor List Dual Band",
        "D": "Fast SSID Change"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "180",
      "source_id": "72",
      "type": "single",
      "question": "When an access point is seeking to join a wireless LAN controller, which message is sent to the AP-\nManager interface?",
      "question_images": [],
      "options": {
        "A": "DHCP request",
        "B": "DHCP discover",
        "C": "discovery response",
        "D": "discovery request"
      },
      "answer": [
        "D"
      ],
      "answer_images": [],
      "explanation": "The LAPs always connect to the management interface address of the controller first with\na discovery request. The controller then tells the LAP the Layer 3 AP-manager interface (which\ncan also be the management by default) IP address so the LAP can send a join request to the AP-\nmanager interface next.\nReference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/wireless/5500-series-wireless-\ncontrollers/119286-lap-notjoin-wlc-tshoot.html",
      "explanation_images": [],
      "question_vi": "Khi một access point đang tìm cách tham gia wireless LAN controller, thông điệp nào được gửi đến AP-Manager interface?",
      "options_vi": {
        "A": "DHCP request",
        "B": "DHCP discover",
        "C": "Discovery response",
        "D": "Discovery request"
      }
    },
